title: Enter Shikari - The Mindsweep (2015) [Japanese Edition]
description:
Enter Shikari are a British rock band formed in St Albans, Hertfordshire, England in 2003. They are named after Shikari, a boat belonging to vocalist Rou Reynolds' uncle. Their debut album, Take to the Skies, was released on 19 March 2007 and reached number 4 in the Official UK Album Chart; their second album, Common Dreads, was released on 15 June 2009 and debuted on the UK Albums Chart at number 16; and their third album, A Flash Flood of Colour, was released on 16 January 2012 and debuted on the chart at number 4. Enter Shikari then spent a considerable amount of time supporting the release through the A Flash Flood of Colour World Tour, before beginning work on a fourth studio album, The Mindsweep, which was released in January 2015. The band has had the same four members since formation.
The Mindsweep is the fourth studio album .
